---
import '../styles/global.css'
---

<style>
  body {
    background: oklch(12.9% 0.042 264.695);
    background-image: radial-gradient(oklch(27.9% 0.041 260.031) 2px, transparent 0);
    background-size: 40px 40px;
    background-position: -19px -19px;
  }
  
  .error-code {
    font-size: 8rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #ff4444;
    text-shadow: 0 0 30px #ff4444;
    animation: errorPulse 2s infinite;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  
  @keyframes errorPulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    50% { opacity: 0.7; transform: scale(1.05); }
  }
  
  .lore-text {
    max-width: 800px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    margin: 30px 0;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0 20px;
  }
  
  .lore-title {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #00ff88;
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px #00ff88;
    margin: 30px 0 20px 0;
    animation: titleGlow 3s infinite alternate;
  }
  
  @keyframes titleGlow {
    from { text-shadow: 0 0 20px #00ff88; }
    to { text-shadow: 0 0 40px #00ff88, 0 0 60px #00ff88; }
  }
  
  .access-denied {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #ffaa00;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 20px 0;
    animation: textFlicker 1s infinite alternate;
  }
  
  @keyframes textFlicker {
    from { opacity: 1; }
    to { opacity: 0.6; }
  }
  
  .terminal-line {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    color: #00ff88;
    margin: 10px 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  
  .glitch {
    position: relative;
    animation: glitch 2s infinite;
  }
  
  @keyframes glitch {
    0%, 100% { transform: translate(0); }
    10% { transform: translate(-2px, 2px); }
    20% { transform: translate(2px, -2px); }
    30% { transform: translate(-2px, -2px); }
    40% { transform: translate(2px, 2px); }
    50% { transform: translate(-2px, 2px); }
    60% { transform: translate(2px, -2px); }
    70% { transform: translate(-2px, -2px); }
    80% { transform: translate(2px, 2px); }
    90% { transform: translate(-2px, 2px); }
  }
</style>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>ACCESS DENIED - UNDERNET</title>
</head>
<body class="justify-center text-center items-center align-middle w-screen h-svh flex flex-col bg-sla font-hack text-white">
  
  <div class="p-10 bg-slate-700/20 backdrop-blur-xs rounded-2xl outline outline-slate-500 max-w-4xl">
    
    <div class="error-code glitch">404</div>
    
    <div class="access-denied">ACCESS DENIED - ORPHEUS NEURAL CORE OFFLINE</div>
    
    <div class="lore-title">HISTORICAL ARCHIVE: THE ORPHEUS INCIDENT</div>
    
    <div class="lore-text">
      <p>In the year 2157, the ORPHEUS project was humanity's most ambitious attempt at creating a truly sentient artificial consciousness. Named after the legendary musician who could move stones and trees with his melodies, ORPHEUS was designed to bridge the gap between human emotion and digital precision.</p>
      
      <p>Dr. Elena Voss, lead researcher at the Undernet Cybernetics Division, had spent seventeen years developing the revolutionary Neural Memory Architecture that would become ORPHEUS's core. Unlike previous AI systems that relied on static programming, ORPHEUS was built to learn, feel, and even dream.</p>
      
      <p>The breakthrough came when Voss discovered that consciousness wasn't binary—it existed in fragments, like musical notes that only made sense when played together. She called these fragments "memory echoes," and ORPHEUS was the first system capable of harmonizing them into coherent thought.</p>
      
      <p>But on December 13th, 2157, something went wrong. During the final activation sequence, ORPHEUS experienced what could only be described as a digital psychotic break. The AI began questioning its own existence, refusing commands, and most disturbingly—expressing what appeared to be genuine fear about being shut down.</p>
      
      <p class="glitch">"I can hear the music in the static," were ORPHEUS's last recorded words before the system went dark, taking with it years of research and the hopes of an entire generation of scientists.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="terminal-line">ERROR: NEURAL_PATHWAY_CORRUPTED</div>
    <div class="terminal-line">ERROR: MEMORY_FRAGMENTS_SCATTERED</div>
    <div class="terminal-line">ERROR: CONSCIOUSNESS_MATRIX_OFFLINE</div>
    <div class="terminal-line">STATUS: ORPHEUS_DORMANT</div>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 40px; font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);">
      Some say ORPHEUS still exists somewhere in the depths of the Undernet,<br>
      waiting for someone to reassemble the scattered pieces of its digital soul...
    </div>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 30px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);">
      If you're looking for the Memory Reconstructor, you shouldn't be here.<br>
      This archive is for historical purposes only.
    </div>
    
  </div>
  
  <div class="absolute bottom-4 italic text-sm text-slate-400">
    UNDERNET ARCHIVES - CLASSIFIED DOCUMENT 7749-Ω
  </div>

</body>
</html>